      "short_description": "Wastewater Viral Activity Level of COVID-19.",
      "long_description": "Wastewater Viral Activity Level (VAL) of COVID-19. The viral activity level is the scaled number of standard deviations above a dynamic baseline. The baseline is the 10th percentile of the log-transformed and normalized concentration values, which is calculated within a 12 month timeframe every 6 months. This is then scaled, where e is the mathmatical constant, and x is the number of standard deviations: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>V<\/mi><mi>A<\/mi><mi>L<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><msup><mi>e<\/mi><mi>x<\/mi><\/msup><\/mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">VAL = e^{x}<\/annotation><\/semantics><\/math> These values are categorized as very low, low, moderate, high, or very high using the following breakpoints: 1.5, 3, 4.5, and 8.",
